Extension Schema
================

The schema for OSQuery tables is generated by the schema_builder.py
script using annotated header files. The generated schema is imported by
MonoRepo and used to generate the combined schema for all platforms.

To add a new table (or update an existing table)

1.  Create header file for table (use existing tables for reference)
    - use TABLE\_PLUGIN\_NAME to define the table name
    - use TABLE\_PLUGIN\_COLUMNS to list columns
    - use TABLE\_PLUGIN\_COLUMN to define each column
    - add comments with table/column description
2.  If table exists on other platforms (e.g. Windows) check descriptions are consistent
3.  Add header file to TABLE\_PLUGIN\_HDRS in CMakeLists.txt
4.  Run build
5.  Generated schema in 'output/schema' and published to artifactory
